related_items.title: The flying statesmen
description: 1 drawing : crayon, ink brush, and opaque white ; 48.6 x 38.5 cm. (sheet) | World War II editorial cartoon shows a battered man with a globe head rejoicing as four men (labeled "F.D.R., Churchill, Stalin, [and] Chiang") fly over on a flying carpet.  In 1943, Roosevelt and Churchill met Chinese leader Chiang Kai Shek for the first time in Cairo to plan strategy.  Roosevelt and Churchill then flew on to Teheran for another historic first meeting with Soviet leader Joseph Stalin.  Duffy views this as an encouraging event for the Allies.

related_items.title: Mosques in Istanbul and archaeological sites in Bergama, Turkey and Egypt
description: 138 photographic prints : albumen ; 29 x 37 cm. or smaller. | Predominately photographs of mosques in Istanbul, especially the Kariye Camii (Church of St. Saviour in Chora) and Ayasofya Camii (Hagia Sofia). Other mosques included are the Sultanahmet Camii, the Sulemaniye Camii, Rüstem Paşa Camii, Ayazma Camii, Sokollu Mehmed Paşa Camii, Şehzade Camii, Hamidiye Camii, Laleli Camii, Fatih Camii, Nuruosmaniye Camii, Yeni Camii  Nusretiye Camii, Bodrum Camii, Büyük Mecidiye Camii, and Kiliç Ali Paşa Camii,  Kücük Ayasofya Camii (Church of Saints Sergius and Bacchus), and Pertevniyal Valide Sultan Camii. Also depicted is the Saint Irene Church. Photographs of Bergama depict ruins and the town. A few photographs of Egypt by Pascal Sebah include an Arab cemetery and the Mosque of al-Burdayni in Cairo, and the ruins at the Temple of Sobek and Haroeris at Ombos. Portraits portray a Bedouin man, Mehmet VI and the daughter of Caliph Abdulmecid II.

related_items.title: Views of the Jerusalem vicinity, Cairo, and Rome
description: 1 album (106 albumen photoprints) ; 36 x 46 cm. (album) | General views of the Holy Land and other archaeological sites. Includes city gates, mosques, churches, tombs, and cemeteries. Some views of the Egyptian pyramids and sphinxes of Jizah. Ruins of Roman palaces and baths. Portraits of Egyptian men and women, two identified as porter and runner. Several views of tourists sitting among ruins in Jerusalem, one cityscape of Damascus, Syria and one of Alexandria, Egypt showing Pompey's Pillar.
